Document: NavigationLink2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationlink2d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the NavigationLink2D node, which allows defining custom connections between navigation meshes.

Property Descriptions
- bidirectional (bool): If true, the link can be traversed in both directions. If false, it can only be traversed from start_position to end_position. Default: true.
  - Method: set_bidirectional(value: bool)
  - Method: is_bidirectional() -> bool
- enabled (bool): If true, the link is active and will be considered by pathfinding. If false, it is ignored. Default: true.
  - Method: set_enabled(value: bool)
  - Method: is_enabled() -> bool
- end_position (Vector2): The ending position of the navigation link. This position snaps to the nearest polygon in the navigation mesh. The search distance is controlled by NavigationServer2D.map_set_link_connection_radius(). Default: Vector2(0, 0).
  - Method: set_end_position(value: Vector2)
  - Method: get_end_position() -> Vector2
- enter_cost (float): A cost added to the path distance when pathfinding enters this link from another navigation mesh region. Default: 0.0.
  - Method: set_enter_cost(value: float)
  - Method: get_enter_cost() -> float
- navigation_layers (int): A bitfield that determines which navigation layers this link belongs to. These layers are checked during pathfinding requests. Default: 1.
  - Method: set_navigation_layers(value: int)
  - Method: get_navigation_layers() -> int
- start_position (Vector2): The starting position of the navigation link. This position snaps to the nearest polygon in the navigation mesh. The search distance is controlled by NavigationServer2D.map_set_link_connection_radius(). Default: Vector2(0, 0).
  - Method: set_start_position(value: Vector2)
  - Method: get_start_position() -> Vector2
- travel_cost (float): A multiplier applied to the distance traveled along the link when calculating the shortest path. Default: 1.0.
  - Method: set_travel_cost(value: float)
  - Method: get_travel_cost() -> float
---CHUNK---
Document: NavigationLink2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationlink2d.rst
Summary: Describes the methods available for interacting with NavigationLink2D nodes, including getting and setting global positions, managing navigation layers, and accessing the navigation map and RID.

Method: get_global_end_position() → Vector2
Returns the end_position that is relative to the link as a global position.

Method: get_global_start_position() → Vector2
Returns the start_position that is relative to the link as a global position.

Method: get_navigation_layer_value(layer_number: int) → bool
Returns whether or not the specified layer of the navigation_layers bitmask is enabled, given a layer_number between 1 and 32.

Method: get_navigation_map() → RID
Returns the current navigation map RID used by this link.

Method: get_rid() → RID
Returns the RID of this link on the NavigationServer2D.

Method: set_global_end_position(position: Vector2) → void
Sets the end_position that is relative to the link from a global position.

Method: set_global_start_position(position: Vector2) → void
Sets the start_position that is relative to the link from a global position.

Method: set_navigation_layer_value(layer_number: int, value: bool) → void
Based on value, enables or disables the specified layer in the navigation_layers bitmask, given a layer_number between 1 and 32.

Method: set_navigation_map(navigation_map: RID) → void
Sets the RID of the navigation map this link should use. By default the link will automatically join the World2D default navigation map so this function is only required to override the default map.